==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unstratified
<hw>Un*strat"i*fied</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Geol.)</fld>
<def>Not stratified; -- applied to massive rocks, as granite, porphyry,
etc., and also to deposits of loose material, as the glacial till, which
occur in masses without layers or strata.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unstrength</ent>⟦br⟧
